👥 HR Dashboard in Power BI
🎯 Aim
To create an interactive HR dashboard in Power BI to analyze employee distribution, salary, gender ratio, and attrition using visuals and slicers.
🧩 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Power BI Desktop.
2.	Click Home → Get Data → Excel.
3.	Select PowerBI_HR_Dashboard.xlsx and click Load.
4.	Go to Report View.
5.	Insert a Bar Chart and place Department → Axis, EmployeeName → Count.
6.	Insert a Pie Chart and place Gender → Legend, EmployeeName → Count.
7.	Insert a Column Chart and place Department → Axis, Salary → Values.
8.	Insert a Card visual and place EmployeeName → Count.
9.	Insert a Table visual with EmployeeName, Department, Salary, and Experience.
10.	Add a Slicer and drag Department into it.
11.	Add a Slicer and drag Gender into it.
12.	Add a Slicer for Attrition and test the dashboard interactivity.

